Lagos – Enyimba, the 2018 CAF Confederation Cup campaigners, have been rated as the 13th best football club in Africa according to the latest ranking released by Cafonline Wednesday. The only Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) surviving club in the 18 continental competitions climbed four places from 17th spot following their recent outstanding performance in the continental championship. Points in the rankings are determined by the results of clubs in the CAF Champions League and updated over the matches from the second round by a system of increasing points each season. This is even as results ranging from 2009 knockout stages in the CAF Confederation Cup are also put into consideration. Enyimba’s foes in the semifinals of the CAF Confederations Cup, Raja Casablanca rated 20th in the 100 best football club in Africa. Meanwhile, Al-Ahli of Egypt top the poll and are followed by TP Mazembe of the Democratic Republic of Congo, while Esperance of Tunisia are third. In the fourth place are Etoile du Sahel of Tunisia, and Al-Hila of Sudan are in the fifth place. Completing the top 10 are ES Setif of Algeria, Zamalek of Egypt, ASEC Mimosas of Cote d’Ivoire, Wydad Athletic Club of Morocco and AS Vita Club of Congo Kinshasa in descending order. SHOCKING STORY!!! After 9 Years Of Suffering From Weak Erection & Premature Ejaculation, 43 Year Old Man Finally Discovers The Solution That Mysteriously Jerk His Dead Manhood Back To Life, Increased His "Rod" Size, And Now Last 32 Minutes In Bed. Click HERE! 